The paper deals with the problem of matching points in the plane with straight line segments, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus on perfect non-crossing matchings suggests that the paper may also involve combinatorial aspects, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The different optimization variants considered in the paper, such as MinMin and MaxMax, suggest that the paper may also involve game-theoretic aspects, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.GT (game theory). Finally, the efficient algorithms provided for various input point configurations suggest that the paper may also involve algorithmic aspects, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CC (computational complexity).
